  "title": "DevSecOps Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Purpose</strong><br />The team designs, delivers, and operates secure, reliable, and scalable digital platforms to supportpolicy, operations, and service delivery across Singapore’s social service sector. <br />The DevSecOps Engineer plays a key role in embedding security, automation, and operational best practices across the application lifecycle. <br />You will work closely with application engineers, security teams, and cross-functional stakeholders to design, implement, and maintain secure cloud infrastructure, CI/CD pipelines, and operational controls, ensuring systems meet government security and compliance requirements.<br /><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities and Activities:</strong><br /><br />• Design, implement, and maintain CI/CD pipelines to support secure and reliable application delivery<br />• Embed security controls and best practices across the software development lifecycle<br />• Support deployment and operations of applications on cloud platforms<br />• Implement and manage infrastructure as code for cloud resources and environments<br />• Configure and maintain identity, access controls, logging, and monitoring in line with security requirements<br />• Perform security hardening, vulnerability remediation, and operational improvements<br />• Collaborate with developers and security teams to ensure secure-by-design application architecture<br />• Create and maintain technical documentation, runbooks, and operational procedures<br /><br /><strong>Job Requirements </strong><br /><br /><strong>Qualification & Experience</strong><br />• Relevant education qualification in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, or related technical fields• 3–5 years of experience in DevOps, DevSecOps, site reliability engineering, or cloud operations<br />• Cloud or security-related certifications (optional)Skills<br />• Experience in designing and maintaining CI/CD pipelines<br />• Hands-on experience with cloud platforms (e.g. AWS) and cloud-native services<br />• Familiarity with Infrastructure as Code tools and practices (e.g. Terraform, AWS Cloud Formation)<br />• Understanding of application and infrastructure security, including access controls and logging• Experience with monitoring, alerting, and operational support<br />• Exposure to containerization and orchestration technologies• Experience with version control systems (e.g. Git) and automation workflow</p><p>Shortlisted candidate will be reached out .</p>",
